title: Hawaii Statewide GIS Program, Judicial District Boundaries, Hawaii,
name: Hawaii Statewide GIS Program, Judicial District Boundaries, Hawaii,
description:
Judicial District Boundaries for the 8 main Hawaiian Islands.
		
Source:		Judicial Districts are set by Hawaii State Statute (HRS Chapter 3, Section 4-1)

		The statute says that the districts are "for election, taxation, education, city,
		county, and all other purposes...."	

History:	Extracted by OP staff from the 1983 1:24,000 
                USGS Digital Line Graphs.
